---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy policy — Elevatek"
  description="What Elevatek collects, why, and your rights under PIPEDA and Québec's Law 25."
  noindex={true}
  minimalFooter={true}
>
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
  </div></section>
  <div class="wrap"><div class="page">
    <p class="updated">Draft — last updated June 2026</p>
    <div class="flag">Draft for review. Confirm with counsel before launch, and fill in the form provider and analytics tool once chosen.</div>

    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>Elevatek is a trade name of Elevatek Consulting Inc., a company incorporated in Québec, Canada. For anything privacy-related, write to <a href="mailto:info@elevatek.ca">info@elevatek.ca</a>. Our designated privacy officer can be reached at the same address.</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>When you use the contact form, we receive what you typed: your name, work email, company, role, stack details, and your message. When you subscribe to the newsletter, we keep your email address. Our hosting provider keeps standard server logs. If you book a call, scheduling runs through Calendly, which receives the details you enter there. <!-- TODO: name the form provider and analytics tool here once chosen --></p>

    <h2>Why we collect it</h2>
    <p>To reply to you, to scope and deliver consulting work you ask us about, and to send the newsletter you signed up for. We don't sell or rent your information, and we don't use it for advertising.</p>

    <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
    <p>Contact submissions are kept as long as needed to handle your request and any engagement that follows. Newsletter emails are kept until you unsubscribe, which you can do from any issue.</p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>Under PIPEDA and Québec's Law 25, you can ask what personal information we hold about you, ask us to correct it, or ask us to delete it. Email <a href="mailto:info@elevatek.ca">info@elevatek.ca</a> and we'll handle it.</p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>This site works without tracking cookies. <!-- TODO: update if analytics is added; Law 25 requires consent for non-essential cookies --></p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>If this policy changes, the date above changes with it.</p>
  </div></div>
</Base>
